This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new network architecture for planning in partially observable environments. It also involves learning to access memory and plan, which are key components of AI. 

The paper is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a neural network to learn to plan and access memory. 

Additionally, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as planning and memory are important components of robotics. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed network architecture uses convolutions to extract features from the environment. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training a neural network to learn to plan and access memory.
